Can you provide an example of a tangible item in Ruby language using descriptive words to denote its properties, characteristics, and features?
Here is an example code:
class Car
  attr_accessor :make, :model, :year, :color, :mileage
  def initialize(make, model, year, color, mileage)
    @make = make
    @model = model
    @year = year
    @color = color
    @mileage = mileage
  end
  def description
    "This car is a #{color} #{make} #{model} from #{year} with #{mileage} miles."
  end
end
my_car = Car.new("Toyota", "Camry", 2020, "blue", 5000)
puts my_car.description
This code creates a Car class with properties such as make, model, year, color, and mileage. An instance of the Car class is then created with specific values for each property. The description method prints out a descriptive sentence about the car's properties, characteristics, and features.
